* fix xml:base (elfeed open relative link from one article to another. make sure this doesn't mess up homepage link)
* implement "recent posts" below posts?
* author-editor separation (feed author separate from post author)
* out-of-source-tree posts directory? (so the ssg [compiler] is separate from the posts programs)
* license

URL choice:
- walters.app/article/bootstrapping-bun
- walters.app/posts/bootstrapping-bun

URLs:
- https://walters.app/ <-- 200
  implemented by reading index.html and serving with no translation
  future: markdown support (Vary: Accept)
- https://walters.app/blog/feed.atom <-- 200
- https://walters.app/blog <-- 200
  implemented by reading posts.html and serving with no translation
  future: generate + cache
  future: markdown support
- https://walters.app/blog/ <-- 308 to blog
- https://walters.app/blog/bootstrapping-bun <-- 200
  implemented by reading posts/bootstrapping-bun.html and serving with no translation
  future: markdown support
- https://walters.app/blog/bootstrapping-bun/ <-- 308 to bootstrapping-bun
- https://walters.app/blog/bootstrapping-bun.html <-- 308 to bootstrapping-bun
- https://walters.app/blog/bootstrapping-bun/index.html <-- 404

Rationale: important to not distinguish between collections and individual resources (in other words, a collection is a resource) because a resource may become a collection later, e.g. if bootstrapping-bun became a whole series then I would be in a situation where a collection is forced to *not* have a trailing slash to maintain old links / ranking.

Fields:
* Slug (immutable)
* Title
* Synopsis
* Content
* License
* Created at
* Updated at
* Checked for relevance at (is this the same as updated)

P0
* Memory caching in nginx(?)
* Cache headers (Cache-Control, ETag, Last-Modified)
* Directory listing
* Atom (ensure Content-Type)
* Dark/light theme
* iOS 12 compatibility
* no-js capable
* Header/footer accents
* Line numbers on code blocks (that aren't copied along with content)

P1
* Copy links on headers
* Sitemap

P2
* Privacy policy
* Email subscription (<details><summary></details>)
* Basic privacy-preserving analytics
	* top-highlight.js
	* events
		* page load
		* JS / no-JS
		* abandon
		* text highlight
		* scroll
		* link click
		* interact w/ subscription box
	* tags
		* IP
		* UA
		* Cookie?
		* Referer

P3
* License
* WebSub
* receiving WebMention
* serve markdown depending on content-type

